issue_comments.body:
Actually I don't know how to distribute it on F-Droid, if there is anyone who want to help me I would appreciate to distribute :)

Currently you can get the lastest APK in [this link](https://github.com/mthli/Tweetin/releases/download/v5.0.0/Tweetin.5.0.0.apk).

In fact it seems like F-Droid builds everything from source, so it might be [quite complicated](https://f-droid.org/wiki/page/Inclusion_Policy) to submit new apps. The easier way is just to make a post on [the F-Droid's forum](https://f-droid.org/forums/forum/submission-queue/). However, I'm not sure if anybody could do this or just the author of the app themselves -- so it would be better if you've done this. :)
Go to their wiki page https://f-droid.org/wiki/page/Main_Page and see the links "Inclusion policy" and "Inclusion how-to". That should clear it up.
Do not cry anymore, stand up and lu it

It's currently [in my repo](https://apt.izzysoft.de/fdroid/index/apk/io.github.mthli.Tweetin) – but as it seems the project is dead (see #3), and there was no update for ~2.5 years, it probably will be removed there soon – unless there's a statement by @mthli that he's going to pick up again :wink:
Looks like. @mthli hasn't been much active on Github recently, the last commit is more than 2 years ago, and there was no answer to any of the issues here made by him since either :disappointed:
